ested-versions` integrity.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:53:- Validation that every metadata entry uses `typeReachable` and stays inside `allowed-packages`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:75:- `latest/libraries.json` — per-library metrics.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:76:- `latest/metrics-over-time.svg` — historical chart referenced from [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:111:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:129:<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:135:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries; each entry's required fields are `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:139:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:143:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:146:If neither matches and the user has enabled `useLatestVersion` on the query (Gradle: `useLatestMetadataVersion()`), the plugin falls back to the entry with `latest: true` (at most one per file, FR-M-6). Otherwise no metadata is loaded for that coordinate. `skipped-versions` is consumed by the test harness and the libraries-and-frameworks page, not by the plugin at native-image time.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:151:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\"}\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:152:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:154:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:157:    UseLatestOpt -- yes --> Latest{\"Any entry with<br/><code>latest: true</code>?\"}\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:158:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:176:- **FR-M-2** Every metadata entry must use [Conditional Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/#specifying-reflection-metadata-in-json) (`typeReachable`) so registration is gated on actual reachability.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:177:- **FR-M-3** Every metadata entry's `typeReachable` condition must reference a class inside the artifact's `allowed-packages`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:190:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-NI-2** `future-defaults-all` is run only against early-access / `latest` / `dev` GraalVM builds, both locally (via `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`) and in scheduled CI lanes that explicitly opt in via `ci.json`'s `nativeImageModeJavaVersions`.\nforge/do-work.sh:336:    log \"Updating metadata-forge to the latest origin/${MONITORED_BRANCH}.\"\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:194:  for translating that into `-H:ConfigurationFileDirectories=...`. No\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:295:| `-PmetadataConfigDirs=<dir1,dir2,...>` | no | Comma-separated absolute paths translated to `-H:ConfigurationFileDirectories=...`. Omitted on the first iteration. |\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:376:                    \"latest\": true,\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:377:                    \"allowed-packages\": %s,\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:378:                    \"metadata-version\": \"%s\",\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:379:                    \"tested-versions\": %s\n./forge/do-work.sh:336:    log \"Updating metadata-forge to the latest origin/${MONITORED_BRANCH}.\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:643:    return \"Stats from `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`:\\n\\n\" + \"\\n\\n\".join(sections)\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:663:            \"\\n### Stats from `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\\n\\n\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:667:    lines = [\"\", \"### Stats from `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\", \"\"]\n./metadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/index.json:3:    \"latest\" : true,\n./metadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/index.jso